<br>
50 Blunt <br>
42 Parry <br>
39 Celtic Dual<br>
6 Shield<br>
and 4 points left over.<br>
<br>
This gives me a total of 2979 points when everything is said and done, but recently it's come to my attention that the formula to determine our points is &quot;a little strange&quot; quoting a CSR I spoke with today when he examined a few different level 50 Bladmasters. It seems that a few are gaining 5 additional points for a total of 2984 which while 5 points doesn't sound like much can really help out. What I need people to do is post what your complete spec (including any other weapon specs and left over points), your characters name, and your server. I'm trying to gather as much data on this as possible. Any one that can help me out would be appreciate so I can email it all to the CSR to investigate further. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shanahankilbeggin>Shanahan Kilbeggin</A> at: 10/31/02 1:08:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shanahankilbeggin>Shanahan Kilbeggin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#000000>(10/31/02 1:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Total Blademaster Spec points</span><hr size=1> Also, if you could add your race as well. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shanahankilbeggin>Shanahan Kilbeggin</A> at: 10/31/02 7:22:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#000000>(10/31/02 5:59 pm)</font>